# Secrets

This repo splits secrets by consumer, and uses agenix for ONE thing only.

## agenix â€” system / service secrets (host-key scoped) ONLY

agenix here manages exclusively the credentials a SYSTEM service needs at boot,
with no human present:

- `nixarm-tunnel-token.age`, `nixrpi-tunnel-token.age`, `nixamd-tunnel-token.age`
  â€” Cloudflare remotely-managed tunnel CONNECTOR TOKENS (one line
  `TUNNEL_TOKEN=â€¦`), consumed by the hardened `cloudflared-connector` unit
  (`modules/nixos/cloudflared.nix`) via `EnvironmentFile`. Encrypted to the host
  key so the host decrypts at activation (+ the personal key so they can be
  re-encrypted). UNIFORM MODEL: all three NixOS hosts (`nixarm`/`nixrpi`/`nixamd`)
  ship their token encrypted to the personal key ONLY â€” NO prebake, NO pinned host
  key. After a host's first boot, its own generated `/etc/ssh` host key is added as
  a recipient and the token re-encrypted via the agenix-host-rekey skill, so the
  host itself decrypts at activation. Decrypted by system agenix during NixOS activation,
  before login. These are scope-tight, ~permanent
  tokens, so their one-time presence in git is accepted (no ongoing rotation = no
  commit churn). The token, tunnel, and proxied CNAME are provisioned in the
  Cloudflare account by `scripts/cf-one-provision.sh` (no `cloudflared tunnel
  login`, no cert.pem, no local credentials JSON).

Recipients are declared per-file in `secrets.nix` (public keys only).

Encrypt / re-encrypt (rarely needed):

    agenix -e secrets/<name>.age          # needs a recipient's private key

Without nix/agenix on the Mac, use plain age to all recipients:

    age -r "<userKey>" -r "<host pubkey>" -o secrets/<name>.age < plaintext

Round-trip verify by sha256 (never echo the value). Commit the resulting `.age`.

HAZARD: SSH host keys double as age identities. Rotating/reimaging a host's
/etc/ssh/ssh_host_ed25519_key silently breaks decryption of every host-scoped
`.age` at next activation â€” re-run the agenix-host-rekey skill after any
host-key change.

## PERSONAL tokens â€” NOT in agenix, NOT in this repo

Personal access tokens (GitHub, HuggingFace, LiteLLM, AWS Bedrock, RunPod,
Vast, Civitai, Cloudflare API, GitLab, Docker Hub, Claude) were REMOVED from
agenix: each rotation produced a committed `.age` blob = version-control churn.
They now live host-locally, never in git:

- macOS (nixcon): raw env-var tokens live in the login **Keychain**
  (`security add-generic-password -s NAME -w`), exported by the host-local
  `~/.zprofile` via `security find-generic-password -w -s NAME`. This is host
  config, NOT managed by this flake or the chezmoi dotfiles repo.
- Login-style tokens: one-time CLI login per machine â€” `gh auth login`,
  `huggingface-cli login`, `docker login`, `glab auth login`, claude login.
  (This is also how devcontainers have always worked.)

Rotating a personal token = update Keychain / re-login. Zero commits, ever.

NOTE: the 13 personal `.age` files removed in this refactor remain in git
HISTORY (old ciphertext, decryptable with the personal key). True revocation =
rotate those tokens at their providers.
